		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.codyscuentos.com/?p=420</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=275509234"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-421" title="codyscuentos_aac" src="http://www.codyscuentos.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/codyscuentos_aac.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" /></a>If you subscribe to the Cody&#8217;s Cuentos podcast via <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=275509234" target="_self">iTunes</a> or any other RSS service, I need you to resubscribe. Feedburner, the service that I use to notify listeners of new episodes, was purchased by Google awhile back.&#8230;</p>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=275509234"><img class="alignright size-medium wp-image-421" title="codyscuentos_aac" src="http://www.codyscuentos.com/wp-content/uploads/2009/01/codyscuentos_aac.jpg" alt="" width="300" height="300" /></a>If you subscribe to the Cody&#8217;s Cuentos podcast via <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=275509234" target="_self">iTunes</a> or any other RSS service, I need you to resubscribe. Feedburner, the service that I use to notify listeners of new episodes, was purchased by Google awhile back. I think it may have been almost two years ago. In any case, yesterday was the day that <strong>my Feedburner account was moved to Google and, in the process, almost all of my subscribers were left behind</strong>. Poof! Gone. Vanished into thin air.</p>
<p>It&#8217;s an unbelievably terrible situation and Google is not providing any answers as to whether or not these people can be recovered. So the only recourse I&#8217;m left with is to ask all of you to resubscribe to the podcast. If you&#8217;ve never subscribed, now would be a great time to do so. <strong>Subscribing is free</strong> and is the best way to receive Cody&#8217;s audio stories as soon as they go online. Depending on the way you wish to receive the audio stories, they will either be emailed to you automatically or download directly to your computer every time a new story is available.</p>
<p><strong>Here&#8217;s what to do now</strong>:</p>
<p>If you subscribe to the podcast via iTunes, <a href="http://itunes.apple.com/WebObjects/MZStore.woa/wa/viewPodcast?id=275509234" target="_blank">visit Cody&#8217;s Cuentos page in iTunes</a> and click the SUBSCRIBE button.</p>
<p>If you prefer,<a href="http://feedburner.google.com/fb/a/mailverify?uri=codyscuentos&amp;loc=en_US"> subscribe to Cody&#8217;s Cuentos by email.</a></p>
<p>If you receive your podcast updates through an RSS reader, <a href="http://feeds2.feedburner.com/codyscuentos" target="_self">click here</a> to add Cody&#8217;s Cuentos.</p>
<p>Sorry for the hassle and please let me know if you encounter any problems. Thank you.</p>
