		<title>Los pollitos dicen</title>
		<link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/codyscuentos/~3/EKc_5uDHyPY/</link>
		<comments>http://www.codyscuentos.com/2008/09/los-pollitos-dicen/#comments</comments>
		<pubDate>Wed, 10 Sep 2008 03:21:47 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator>voicesenespanol@gmail.com (codyscuentos.com)</dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Announcements]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[bilingual]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[bilingual in the boonies]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[carrie ferguson weir]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[los pollitos dicen]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.codyscuentos.com/?p=118</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[<p><em><span style="font-family: Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: #cc3300; font-size: small;">Los pollitos dicen pío, pío, pío<br />
cuando tienen hambre, cuando tienen frío.<br />
La gallina busca el maíz y el trigo<br />
Les da la comida y les presta abrigo.<br />
Bajo de sus alas duérmen los pollitos<br /></span></em>&#8230;</p>]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p><em><span style="font-family: Verdana,Arial,Helvetica,sans-serif; color: #cc3300; font-size: small;">Los pollitos dicen pío, pío, pío<br />
cuando tienen hambre, cuando tienen frío.<br />
La gallina busca el maíz y el trigo<br />
Les da la comida y les presta abrigo.<br />
Bajo de sus alas duérmen los pollitos<br />
Acurrucaditos hasta el otro día.</span></em></p>
<p><em>The little chicks say peep, peep, peep<br />
when they are hungry, when they are cold.<br />
The mother hen looks for corn and wheat<br />
she gives them food, and grants them shelter.<br />
Under mama’s wings, huddling up,<br />
Sleep the little chicks until the next day. </em></p>
<p><em><strong>Los pollitos dicen</strong></em> is the title of a popular lullaby sung in Latin America. It&#8217;s also <a href="http://www.lospollitosdicen.biz" target="_self">the name of a company</a> run by Cuban-American entreprenuer Carrie Ferguson Weir. <a title="Voices en español" href="http://spanish-podcast.com/2008/09/09/los-pollitos-dicen-combining-two-cultures/" target="_self">Listen to the podcast</a> I did with Carrie about growing up Cuban-American in Miami and how she came to develop a T-shirt line for babies.</p>
<p>Besides being a businesswoman and working mom, Carrie also writes an enjoyable blog about her life. It&#8217;s called <a href="http://www.bilingualintheboonies.com" target="_self">Bilingual in the Boonies</a>.</p>
<p><img style="vertical-align: top;" src="http://spanish-podcast.com/wp-content/uploads/2008/09/animation.gif" alt="Los Pollitos Dicen" width="300" height="300" /></p>
